text: Zdice is a town in the Beroun District in the Central Bohemian Region of the Czech Republic. It has about 4,200 inhabitants. ==History== Until 1918, the town was part of the Austrian monarchy (Austria side after the compromise of 1867), in the Hořovice district, one of the 94 Bezirkshauptmannschaften (district administrative authorities) in Bohemia.Die postalischen Abstempelungen auf den österreichischen Postwertzeichen-Ausgaben 1867, 1883 und 1890, Wilhelm Klein, 1967 ==Notable people== *Josef Vorel (1801–1874), priest and composer ==References== Category:Cities and towns in the Czech Republic Category:Populated places in the Beroun District
title: Zdice
